author: Good Enough
description:
San Quentin State Prison is California’s oldest and most notorious correctional facility. Opened in 1852, it has housed some of the most infamous criminals in American history. From its death row to its role in prison reform programs, San Quentin remains a symbol of both fear and transformation.
